/////////
Step to create package.json
//////////////
**NodeJs must be installed in your system
> navigate to the folder using cmd/terminal
> npm init
> Answer all questions
> type "yes"

>>>>>>>>>><<<<<<<<<<<<
//////
How to install package
/////////
> navigate to the folder using cmd/terminal
> npm i packagename

> npm i 

by default alaways latest version
for specific version (npm i react@16.2.1)


/////////////
create-react-app
//////////

>>>>>
local dependency > local to folder

global dependency > local to system
> need admin access to install
> they will not add in package.json
> they are just used generate application first time

/////Window/////
open cmd as admin 
npm i -g create-react-app

///mac
open terminal
sudo npm i -g create-react-app


////////////////////////
How to generate React app
////////////////////////
?????Window??????

>>>>>Only Time time<<<<<<
open cmd as admin 
npm i -g create-react-app

>>>>Next Every Time<<<<<<<
> go inside the folder where you want app 
> create-react-app appname

------------------------------
?????Mac/Linux??????
>>>>>Only Time time<<<<<<
open terminal
sudo npm i -g create-react-app

>>>>Next Every Time<<<<<<<
> go inside the folder where you want app 
> create-react-app appname

React > main lib
ReactDOM > help to render display the content on screen
ReactScript > help to run application


////////////////////////
How to start React app
////////////////////////
> go inside app folder
> npm start 
> http://localhost:3000



State Props


state
> State act like a local variable
> state can be defined in class component
> value of state can be updated in same component
> any data intercation will happen through state

Props
> help to pass data from one component to another
> value of props cannot be updated



ComponentA                ====>    ComponentB
State=data from Api       props    we can recive data from props

